{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b3d5673-7038-44f2-b5b7-a3d99589ecee","content":"Here's your complete migration plan from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP):\n\n---\n\n## Migration Plan: VSTest → Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### Phase 1 — Update NuGet Packages (per test project)\n\nReplace your current package references:\n\n```xml\n<!-- REMOVE these -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestFramework\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestAdapter\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n\n<!-- REPLACE with single meta-package -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` meta-package (≥3.3) bundles framework, adapter, **and** the new runner.\n\n### Phase 2 — Enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\nAdd to each test `.csproj` (or a `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis makes each test project a self-contained executable using MTP instead of `vstest.console`.\n\n### Phase 3 — TRX Reporting\n\nAdd the TRX extension package:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n```\n\nRun with: `dotnet test --results-directory ./TestResults -- --report-trx`\n\n### Phase 4 — Code Coverage\n\nAdd:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n```\n\nRun with: `dotnet test -- --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n\n### Phase 5 — Azure DevOps Pipeline Changes\n\nReplace:\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n# AFTER\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- --report-trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n    searchFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Phase 6 — Validate\n\n1. `dotnet build` — all 5 projects produce executables\n2. `dotnet test` — tests run via MTP (look for \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" in output)\n3. Verify `.trx` files are generated\n4. Verify coverage reports are generated\n5. Pipeline publishes results correctly\n\n### Key Notes\n\n| Concern | Detail |\n|---------|--------|\n| **Parallel execution** | MTP runs each project as a process; use `--parallel` on `dotnet test` for project-level parallelism. In-process parallelism still works via `[Parallelize]`. |\n| **Filters** | `--filter` works the same: `dotnet test --filter \"Category=Unit\"` |\n| **Runsettings** | Still supported via `--settings file.runsettings` |\n| **Rollback** | Remove `EnableMSTestRunner`/`OutputType` to revert to VSTest at any time |\n\nMigrate one project first, validate in CI, then roll out to the remaining four.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d98b3177-9aa4-4311-8b97-aa0b125005d2","outputTokens":935,"requestId":"E3C4:207F19:504063:5CC119:6A052257"},"id":"76862bd2-2090-460f-b4f3-5dde483fc16d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:16:25.559Z","parentId":"785646e7-b385-4978-85bd-9f800cab8028"}
